In [9]: class Perceptron:
def __init__(self):
self.alpha = 0.05
self.paras =[]
def w_x_b(self, x):
return np.dot(self.W, x) + self.b
#
def fit(self, X, Y):
self.W = np.ones(X.shape[1], dtype = np.float32)
self.b = -5
x0_mean = np.mean(X[0])
x1_mean = np.mean(X[1])
self.W[0] = x1_mean/x0_mean
print(self.W, self.b)
self.paras = [(self.W, self.b)]
finish = False
while not finish:
finish = True
for index in range(len(X)):
x = X[index]
y = Y[index]
if y * self.w_x_b(x) <= 0:
# +=
self.W = self.W + self.alpha * y * x
self.b = self.b + self.alpha * y
finish = False
self.paras.append((self.W, self.b))
if finish:
return 'Perceptron training completed!'

model = Perceptron()
model.fit(X, Y)
